content: hello everyone and welcome to Analyse lesson
In August, a tournament was played in Karepa, Estonia
what made it interesting, was the tournament rules that were tested
how many of you know the Tarannikov rule ? or, 5 reverse rule ?
it is an insteresting and hard rule
1st player places a stone in middle
2nd stone must be attached to it
3rd stone must form a renju opening
4th move must be within 7x7 range from the 1st stone
and 5th move must be within 9x9 range from the 1st
is that after each move made
So, it's possible, that the starting player gets to put all 5 first stones
it means that YAODAO opening can be used
I participated in this tournament also, along with many Estonians and few other Finnish and Russian players
also, some visitors from Russia, Latvia and Czech played
today, I will shortly show you all of my poor games from this tournament :)
but, as usual, before starting let's warm up a bit

For me, the results 4points was quite enough, the tournament was more about fun and testing new rules

I'm sorry, the lesson was so long
but here are your cp's and I thank you all for coming today!
